{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9cca93ab-2ae7-4195-bc43-269b8ff440a9","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **drops support** for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (minimum is `net6.0`) |\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. **Consolidate packages** — MSTest v3 uses a single `MSTest` package instead of separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79976237-dbef-4d2f-8412-6cc9d23bb6e8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **MSTest v3 drops support for older frameworks.** MSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package or `MSTest.TestFramework` 3.x) requires at minimum:\n   - .NET 6.0+ (for .NET Core/modern .NET)\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2+ (this one should be fine since they have net462)\n   \n   Actually, let me be more precise. MSTest v3 requires:\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later\n   - .NET 6.0 or later (dropped support for .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0)\n\n2. So the user will have issues with:\n   - `net5.0` — .NET 5.0 is out of support and MSTest v3 doesn't support it\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` — .NET Core 3.1 is out of support and MSTest v3 doesn't support it\n   - `net462` — This should be fine, MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n\n3. MSTest v3 also consolidates everything into a single `MSTest` package rather than splitting it across separate framework and adapter packages.","outputTokens":593,"requestId":"CFCE:1BCB52:6312E90:6F20CB0:69EC26AD"},"id":"a0ea7060-3ea7-4d87-b989-02bbaf690173","timestamp":"2026-0